The paper discusses the use of data compression algorithms and artificial intelligence methods for time series forecasting, which are topics commonly studied in the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of Mean Absolute Error (MAE) as an accuracy measure, which is a common metric used in information theory (cs.IT) and data science (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the automatic selection of the best compression algorithm, which involves optimization and decision-making, topics commonly studied in software engineering (cs.SE).
